## Summary

Your project is already **8/10** — the modular architecture, risk engine with LLM, pessimistic locking, and live deployment are genuinely impressive. The gap to **11/10** is mostly about:

1. **Proving you can think about failure modes** (idempotency, rate limiting)
2. **Proving you test your code** (30+ meaningful tests)
3. **Proving you ship production-ready systems** (observability, structured logging)
4. **Removing dead code and learning artifacts** (unused Kafka/Redis deps, tutorial comments)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The single most impactful thing you can do right now: **Implement idempotency + expand tests + add actuator**. These three together transform the project from "a well-structured student project" to "this person has shipped production software."
